mappings.description:
Each device and soil probe has a logical slot that drives its entity IDs (sf_dp1_temperature, sf_dp1_soil1_moisture). Soil probes are scoped to the device they're plugged into — dp1_soil1 and dp2_soil1 are different probes. Current mappings:

{mappings}

Edit any slot below. Soil fields accept device-prefixed (dp1_soil2) or bare (soil2) values; the device prefix is fixed by where the probe is physically attached. To REPLACE a probe, give the new serial the old slot and BLANK the old serial (blank = retire). Entity IDs re-align after the integration reloads.
